highlight
=========

Colorize a regex in terminal text, because Select-String (PowerShell) does not have this. Cross-platform.

Build:
$ cargo build --release

Regexes are according to https://doc.rust-lang.org/regex/regex/index.html

Usage:

$ highlight <regex> [files]...

If no files are provided, the input will be read from stdin.
(-> piping into 'highlight' is possible)